  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean, low-confidence honestly documented)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are fully assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. One factor (Model form) carries an explicitly-flagged low-confidence score with wide uncertainty bounds; this limitation is documented honestly with full rationale and accepted as residual risk with offset rationale. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Decision: Accepted.",
